{
  "texts": [
    "However, ethically relevant conceptual issues still arise: computational models of the brain are not digital replicas of brains; instead they replicate very specific and targeted brain functions.",
    "As a result, their level of fidelity to their physical counterpart is more limited than the term might suggest to non-expert publics.",
    "However, if non-expert publics are aware of the creation of digital twins of the brain, they are likely to infer the existence of a type of entity that is different from what these models actually represent [23].",
    "This is one reason for finding the use of terms such as \"digital twin\" to refer to these models problematic.",
    "Similar points have been made regarding the use of the term \"mini brain\" to refer to brain organoids [5]."
  ]
}